<TITLE> WTO probes EU complaint against US anti-dumping </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 GENEVA, June 4 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The World Trade Organisation (WTO) on Monday launched a new probe at the request of the European Union into US anti-dumping measures on EU exports of goods ranging from steel to pasta and chemicals. The WTO's Dispute Settlement Body (DSB) agreed automatically to an inquiry because it was the second time that Brussels had made the request for an investigation. The investigation involves the use of so-called "zeroing" in the calculation of possible anti-dumping duties, a practice already ruled illegal by the WTO in a number of different cases. The probe by a panel of WTO trade judges can take up to 9 months to reach a verdict
